FBIS4-51314 "drchi103_g_94003" FBIS-CHI-94-103 Daily Report 26 May 1994 Sub-Saharan Africa Beijing Offers Establishment of Relations With Malawi Beijing Offers Establishment of Relations With Malawi OW2705024894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1258 GMT 26 May 94 OW2705024894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service Chinese BFN [Text] Beijing, May 26 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin recently sent a message to Elson Bakili Muluzi, congratulating him on his election as the new president of Malawi. In the telegram, Jiang Zemin said that the recent smooth national election and the subsequent formation of a new government headed by Muluzi have opened up a new chapter in Malawi's history. Jiang expressed the belief that under the leadership of President Muluzi, Malawi would succeed in its cause of national construction and economic development. He said that although China and Malawi have not been in contact with each other for many years, the Chinese people have always cherished a friendly affection for the people of Malawi. China is willing to establish and develop friendly and cooperative relations with Malawi on the basis of the five principles of peaceful coexistence and believes that the friendship between the people of the two countries will enjoy development with efforts from both sides, the telegram said.
